                    <blockquote class=""blockquote"">
                        <p class=""mb-0"">Those living the longest and healthiest lives followed a whole-food, plant-based diet.</p>
                    </blockquote>     
                </div>  

                <div class=""col-sm-12 col-md-8 col-lg-9 text-left"" data-aos=""fade-right"" style=""padding:1em 2em;"">
                    <p>My journey to plant-based began by reading Dan Buettner's 2008 book, The Blue Zones, which catalogues his exploration of the longest living peoples on our planet. A true inspiration – I read this book in springtime, accompanied with bread, olives and");
            WriteLiteral(@" a glass of <em>Cannonau di Sardegna</em>.</p>
                    <p>Introduced to the concept of plant-based, Dan's book was followed by studying the work of Ancel Keys and his Seven Countries Study (the original study of the Mediterranean diet), T.C. Campbell and his China Study, as well as the Willcox's study of the Okinawan centenarians. The pattern was obvious; those living the longest and healthiest lives followed a whole-food, plant-based diet.</p> 
